SIMPLE: gratuity
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Gratuity
<hw>Gra*tu"i*ty</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>Gratuities</plw> <pr>(#)</pr>.</plu> <ety>[F.
<ets>gratuit⟦eacute⟧</ets>, or LL. <ets>gratuitas</ets>.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>Something given freely or without recompense; a free
gift; a present.</def> <rj><au>Swift.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Something voluntarily given in return for a favor or
service, as a recompense or acknowledgment.</def> <-- usually money. In
particular, the money given to a waiter, cab driver, bellhop, etc. as a
reward for good service = tip -->⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Gratulate</ent>⟦br⟧
